We allow a temporary exception in this case.  You would develop the AnnotatationHub package that you would submit to the Bioconductor new submission tracker for review. We allow data to be added to the live devel version of the database, with the expectation that the package is going to be submitted and accepted in a timely manner.  If the package is not accepted, we would eventually remove the data from the database as all data is associated with an accompanied Bioconductor package.

If you would like to test on your own before submission, You could use the BiocHubServer code which is documentation on how to create and mimic our database we utilized. https://github.com/Bioconductor/BiocHubServer

Cheers,



Lori Shepherd

Bioconductor Core Team

Roswell Park Comprehensive Cancer Center

Department of Biostatistics & Bioinformatics

