Subject: [Bioc-devel] Bioconductor Release 3.14 Schedule
Message-ID: <MN2PR12MB4094514F1C1AEB0565937000F9DA9@MN2PR12MB4094.namprd12.prod.outlook.com>

The Bioconductor Release 3.14 Schedule has been posted and is tentatively scheduled for Wednesday October 27th. This date is subject to change. Bioconductor 3.14 will use R-devel in preparation for R-4.2.0 Spring release.


Important deadlines can be found on the website and will be posted here and on the bioc-devel at r-project.org mailing list. As a quick summary:


Friday October 1 st: New package submission deadline. Packages will still need to pass the formal review process to be included in Release 3.14; this deadline will ensure at least an initial review of the package. Package submitted after this date are not guaranteed to be reviewed; they will be reviewed time pending.


Monday October 11th Current Release 3.13 Freeze. No changes will be accepted to the Bioconductor 3.13 branch after this date.


Wednesday October 13th No API changes to devel 3.14.


Wednesday October 20th Newly submitted packages need to be accepted by this date to be included in the release


Friday October 22nd Deadline for packages to be passing R CMD install/build/check on Bioconductor builders.


Tuesday October 26th Devel 3.14 branch is frozen to create release branch.


Wednesday October 27th Release Bioconductor 3.14

Cheers,


Lori Shepherd

Bioconductor Core Team

Roswell Park Comprehensive Cancer Center

Department of Biostatistics & Bioinformatics

Elm & Carlton Streets

Buffalo, New York 14263


